Prerequisites:
Kubernetes server installed and configured .

STEP 1:   -----create MySQL server serction-----
choose the correct directory 
for 1 replicatiion use stateful-mysql-only-1-replica-ok directory :
# kubectl apply  mysql-configmap.yaml  mysql-services.yaml  mysql-statefulset.yaml 
 
for 3 replications ( 1 read-write and 2 read-only) choose  stateful-mysql-3-replica-ok directory:
# kubectl apply mysql-configmap.yaml  mysql-pv.yaml  mysql-services.yaml  mysql-statefulset.yaml

STEP 2: ----create ubuntu server with python scripts-----
use the "ubuntu" directory , run all yaml files 
# kubectl apply pv-claim.yaml  pv-volume.yaml  ubuntu.yaml

STEP 3: ---create NodeJS server-----
use the "nodejs" directory , run all yaml files 
# kubectl apply nodejs.yaml  pv-claim1.yaml  pv-volume1.yaml


STEP 4: -----check --------------
connect to the ubuntu pod that was created all external scripts are located at  /external  ( mounted to /data/mnt0 of the host)

